    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small tubes of glass, metal, stone, or another material, designed to store cosmetics. Best known as glass works from ancient Egypt, Greece, and Rome. The cosmetic was extracted with a cosmetic stick or other device. Modern examples are made of pliable metal or plastic, and the cosmetic is extruded when pressure is applied.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093897/Metropolitan Museum of Art [online] (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleine buisjes van glas, metaal, steen of een ander materiaal bedoeld om cosmetica in te bewaren. Veel gebruikt in het oude Egypte, Griekenland en Rome. De cosmetica werden uit de buisjes gehaald met een cosmeticastokje of een ander instrument. Tegenwoordig zijn ze gemaakt van buigzaam metaal of kunststof, en wordt de cosmetica eruit gehaald door erop te drukken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>玻璃、金屬、石頭、或其他材料製成的管狀容器，用以貯存化妝品；最著名者為來自古埃及、希臘、與羅馬的玻璃製品。管內之化妝品可用化妝棒或其他工具取出。現代型的化妝管乃軟金屬或塑膠所製，化妝品則以擠壓的方式取出。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
